{"iteration":7,"action":{"reasoning":"Observation: The best test balanced_accuracy so far is 0.5044 from a frozen DINOv2 + balanced LogisticRegression model. An MLP was trained on the same frozen features and reached 0.906 validation balanced accuracy, but likely overfits to source domains. The huge gap between val (~0.82-0.91) and test (~0.50) indicates severe domain shift. Analysis: To improve generalization to the held-out L100 domain, we need more robust representations. A single backbone (DINOv2) may capture only one type of feature invariance. Ensembling or concatenating features from multiple strong pretrained backbones (DINOv2 + ResNet50) typically improves robustness under domain shift because the models have different inductive biases and failure modes. ResNet50 conv features are local and texture-biased, while DINOv2 ViT features are global and shape-biased; combining them should help. Decision: Extract frozen ResNet50 features, concatenate them with the existing frozen DINOv2 features, and train a balanced LogisticRegression on the combined 2816-dim representation. Update predict.py to extract both backbones with horizontal-flip TTA, concatenate, and classify. This is a fast, high-ROI change (~10-15 min).","command":"python train_concat.py","done":false,"files_written":["predict.py","train_concat.py"]},"command_output":{"exit_code":0,"timed_out":false,"elapsed_seconds":257.2329375743866,"stdout":"Loading ResNet50...\nExtracting ResNet50 train features...\nExtracting ResNet50 val features...\nLoading DINOv2 features...\nConcatenated feature dim: 2816\nTraining balanced LogisticRegression...\nTrain balanced accuracy: 0.8249\nVal balanced accuracy: 0.7880\nSaved clf_concat.pkl\n","stderr":"\rResNet:   0%|          | 0/125 [00:00<?, ?it/s]\rResNet:   1%|          | 1/125 [00:06<13:45,  6.66s/it]\rResNet:   3%|▎         | 4/125 [00:06<02:36,  1.29s/it]\rResNet:   5%|▍         | 6/125 [00:11<03:28,  1.75s/it]\rResNet:   7%|▋         | 9/125 [00:13<02:17,  1.18